msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid "The extension requires the URI of the SPIRE Agent's Workload Endpoint socket:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid ""
"If `quarkus.spiffe-client.endpoint-socket` is not set, the extension falls back to the standard `SPIFFE_ENDPOINT_SOCKET` environment variable as defined by the https://spiffe.io/docs/latest/spiffe-specs/spiffe_workload_endpoint/#4-locating-the-endpoint[SPIFFE Workload Endpoint specification].\n"
"This environment variable is typically set by the SPIRE Agent for workloads it manages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid "The URI must use one of the following schemes, as defined by the https://github.com/spiffe/spiffe/blob/main/standards/SPIFFE_Workload_Endpoint.md[SPIFFE Workload Endpoint] specification:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid "`unix://` for Unix Domain Sockets (production default), for example `unix:///run/spire/sockets/agent.sock`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid "`tcp://` for TCP connections (development and testing), for example `tcp://127.0.0.1:8080`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid ""
"For the `tcp` scheme, the host must be an IP address and a port is required.\n"
"Hostnames are not accepted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/security-spiffe-client.adoc
msgid "On Windows, only the `tcp://` scheme is currently supported."
msgstr ""

